<br>
1. Changing the way we do things will undoubtedly break us, even if its only temporarily.<br>
<br>
2. Song choice and timing (twisting) is what sets the good bards apart from the bad bards.<br>
<br>
3. Twisting helps keep fly-by-night twinks/newbs out of our upper level ranks.<br>
<br>
<br>
Honestly, if your wrists are hurting, its a problem with ergonomics. I have 300 days played on my bard and I guarantee you, you can play in pain or you can play without pain. I used to play in pain till I figured out how to position myself so as to not put the strain on my wrists that causes the pain. <br>
<br>
You may also need to change your play style just a tad. You cant expect to chant kite in the same circle for 4 hours straight and not be sore.<br>
<br>
If its not real pain and you just don't like the &quot;pain in the arse&quot; of twisting, then play a different class. There's so many classes that don't require the kind of maintenance that we do. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raiddinn>Raiddinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 300<br> <font color=#330000>(7/4/04 12:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19562.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ~</span><hr size=1> With all due respect there are a lot of people who have been putting in more than 40hrs per week typing for a lot longer and have been playing since way before 01, and there is a lot of people who cant play acceptable bards because they have pain, a lot of them got it from EQ also.<br>
<br>
Limiting people to certain classes because interacting with a service they pay for regularly (note that they pay regularly for every upgrade the company puts out to the product too) causes them RL disabilities is pretty rediculous.<br>
<br>
When I bought this product it didnt have written on the box playing the bard class will cause you and others long term disabilities, and in accordance with that I dont think it should, and since it does I believe that it should be fixed so it doesnt.<br>
<br>
Seriously, pretend your bank offers online banking, and you pay extra money per month that way you can use that service.  But once you get online and try to bank online then you run into the following interface problem:<br>
<br>
W<br>
&lt;Click OK to continue&gt; - Click<br>
<br>
We<br>
&lt;Click OK to continue&gt; - Click<br>
<br>
Wel<br>
Click Click click click click click<br>
<br>
Welcome Mr.<br>
Click x 10,000<br>
<br>
Welcome Mr. ~<br>
Your personal information is ~<br>
Your account balance is ~<br>
<br>
I know, its rediculous, equally as rediculous as playing a bard is atm.<br>
<br>
Impressario Raiddinn the Beatdropper<br>
