<br>
MQ made the game WAY more fun for me. I could talk with my friends and goof around in raid chat with all my guildies and not worry about a song droping. Anything that would cut down on the twisting I think would be a big help and make the game more enjoyable for a majority of the bards that play. I think Fal's idea is a good, reasonable step in the right direction. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jaosbrell>JaosBrell</A> at: 7/8/04 10:20 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=indalor>Indalor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#330000>(7/4/04 6:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19562.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposed solution to the pains of twisting.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> When I bought this product it didnt have written on the box playing the bard class will cause you and others long term disabilities<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
